GQD was prepared by carbonization of citric acid in 200 °C furnace (Scheme 2
                        ). TEM image of GQD showing the <5 nm particle size and demonstrated the successful synthesis of quantum dot using this convenient procedure (Fig. 1
                        ). For PL spectroscopy of synthesized GQD 360, 380 and 400 nm wavelength were used as excitation wavelengths. The excitation-independent emission peaks are given in Fig. 2
                        . As can be seen the color of GQD aqueous solution is pale yellow, but emitted the blue fluorescence under 365 nm UV light. All of these observations, confirmed that GQD was prepared in an appropriate quantum size.

In continue, azide groups were introduce on GQD surface using NaN3 (GQD-N3). The ethynyl ferrocene was reacted with azide groups of GQD-N3 under click condition and triazole ring was formed as mediator for chemically modified of GQD with ferrocene (GQD-Fc) (Scheme 3
                        ). For chemical polymerization of pyrrole, FeCl3 was used as an oxidant and anhydrous ethanol as solvent. Polypyrrole as a conductive polymer was physically mixed with GQD-Fc under sonication in DI water for 2 h in order to preparation of GQD-Fc/PPy nanocomposite (Scheme 4
                        ). Conductive polymers are conductive in nature due to the existence of a conjugated electron or alternating single bond and double bond system in its chemical structure. The PPy structure and synergistic effects between GQD-Fc and PPy especially hydrogen bonding, electrostatic interactions, and π-π stacking which conducive to formation of stable GQD-Fc/PPy nanocomposite has been shown in Fig. 3
                        .
